com.mway.bluerange.android.sdk.core.logging

Class BeaconMessagePersistorImpl

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.mway.bluerange.android.sdk.core.logging.BeaconMessagePersistorImpl
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    BeaconMessagePersistor

    public class BeaconMessagePersistorImpl
extends java.lang.Object
implements BeaconMessagePersistor
    This class is the default implementation of the BeaconMessagePersistor interface. The log has a default maximum size of DEFAULT_MAX_LOG_SIZE. In order to increase performance and compression efficiency and decrease energy consumption, the messages are saved in chunks with a chunk size of chunkSize. The persisting strategy is defined by the FileAccessor. By default, each chunk is compressed with the gzip compression algorithm before it is being saved. However, to increase the persisting efficiency, the compression might be turned off.
